{% # Validation - Preset - Content v2.0.0 %}

{% comment %}
  Changelog
  - v2.0.0 — first real Tier-3 implementation (was a stale scaffold on the old `display: block` harness with a hardcoded column width). token-section is now the real production theme-root grid; the readable column comes from `--content-width` capping the grid's content track (production-faithful), and inter-block rhythm paints through the real theme-root rhythm rule. Harness chrome from `validation--harness-styles`. Per `validation-contract.md` Tier 3.
  - v1.0.1 — drop the original block_rhythm-bug write-up now that the cascade is fixed; replace with a current-behaviour description.
  - v1.0.0 — initial scaffold (composition reference; not tracked as a Tier-3 implementation)

  Tier-3 composition validation for the "content" pattern: a title + richtext +
  button stacked in a readable column. Exercises the cross-block cascade that
  only emerges in composition:

  - Inter-block rhythm: the section's `--block-rhythm` paints as the
    margin-block-start of each block past the first, via the real theme-root
    rhythm rule (`> .shopify-block:not(:first-child)`). The visible gaps between
    title → body → button are the rhythm, cascade-applied.
  - Prose-within-rhythm: the richtext's own paragraph-to-paragraph spacing
    (prose `@layer utilities`) composes with the wider block rhythm — the two
    spacing systems coexist (16px between paragraphs, the rhythm between blocks).
  - content_width caps the readable column; the grid centers it.

  Reachable only at /?view=validation--preset--content.
  See `.context/docs/validation.md` + `validation-contract.md` § Tier 3.
{% endcomment %}

{% liquid
  assign color_scheme = section.settings.color_scheme | default: 'scheme-1'
  assign base_selector = 'shopify-section-' | append: section.id
%}

<token-section data-modifiers="theme-root,color-scheme:{{ color_scheme }}">
  {% render 'validation--breadcrumb' %}

  <header class="validation__intro">
    <h1>Composition: content</h1>
    <p>
      A title + body + button stacked in a <code>content_width</code>-capped readable column. Tier-3 probes the
      inter-block <code>--block-rhythm</code> cascade (each block past the first sits the rhythm distance below the
      previous) coexisting with the richtext's own prose paragraph spacing.
    </p>
  </header>

  {% content_for 'blocks' %}

  {% render 'validation--block-labels', section: section %}
</token-section>

{% capture dynamic_style %}
  /* Cap the grid content track to a readable column (reading width). Inherits to
     token-section, where the theme-root grid reads var(--content-width). */
  --content-width: 42.5rem;
{% endcapture %}
{% render 'utility--dynamic-style', base_selector: base_selector, css_content: dynamic_style %}
{% render 'validation--harness-styles' %}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Preset: content",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "shopify-section--validation--preset--content",
  "blocks": [{ "type": "@theme" }],
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "color_scheme",
      "id": "color_scheme",
      "label": "Color scheme",
      "default": "scheme-1"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
